===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|valva|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈvælv/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A device that controls the flow of a gas or fluid through a pipe.
# A device that admits fuel and air into the cylinder of an internal combustion engine, or one that allows combustion gases to exit.
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} One or more membranous [[partition]]s, flaps, or folds, which permit the passage of the contents of a vessel or [[cavity]] in one direction, but stop or retard the flow in the opposite direction; as, the ileocolic, mitral, and semilunar valves.
# {{context|British|lang=en}} A [[vacuum tube]].
# {{context|botany|lang=en}} One of the pieces into which certain fruits naturally separate when they [[dehisce]].
# {{context|botany|lang=en}} A small portion of certain [[anther]]s, which opens like a [[trapdoor]] to allow the pollen to escape, as in the [[barberry]].
# {{context|biology|lang=en}} One of the pieces or divisions of [[bivalve]] or multivalve shells.
# {{context|biology|lang=en}} One of the two similar portions of the shell of a [[diatom]].

